Nope, that's incorrect.<p>You can opt-in to the "graceful degradation" style of routing by using:<p><pre><code>    Backbone.history.start({
      pushState: true,
      hashChange: false
    });
</code></pre>
... which will route URLs using pushState where available, and will run full-page loads where pushState is not supported.<p>It's a pretty rare use case for a Backbone app that needs a router, but it's definitely supported.
